      "author": "ryanravn",
      "description": "## Fixes\n- **Fix ENOENT crash on sync after id rename.** `PLUGIN_DIR` was hardcoded to `plugins/seafile`, so the plugin tried to read and write its sync data at a path that didn't exist after the rename to `seafile-continued`. Now derived from `manifest.id`.\n- **Fix ENOENT on first sync.** Obsidian's `adapter.append()` throws if the file doesn't exist; the sync data log was only created later. Now `SyncController.init()` creates empty `sync_dlog` and `sync_data` files up front.",
